    <p>ST Face­book users re­acted with sym­pa­thy to the sui­cide near Bukit Timah Na­ture Re­serve, and some shared their own sit­u­a­tions. Tan Tan Serene wrote: “I’ve got two (autis­tic) boys, no helper. The elder boy is quite nor­mal, but my (five-year-old) boy’s mind is like that of a 1.5-year-old tod­dler. I am very stressed. What if I grow old and have no en­ergy to take care liao or die, how? Who looks af­ter him?”</p>
    <p>MRT TRAIN SER­VICE DIS­RUP­TION:</p>
    <p>The re­cent dis­rup­tion to train ser­vices trig­gered anx­i­ety among ST Face­book users on many lev­els, from pri­vate fears (Soh Zheng Kuang said: “My sym­pa­thies go to­wards all with ir­ri­ta­ble bowel syn­drome”) to pub­lic Covid-19 ones (Ji­aDa Chuek wrote: “This was a re­ally cre­ative way of form­ing a new clus­ter! We ran out of clus­ters, so we needed to cre­ate a new one”).</p>


